1. Encapsulation: wrapping related class properties(fields and methods) into one unit. 

Example: java class.

2. Inheritance: reusing the properties of one(parent/base/super) class 
                from another(child/derived/sub) class.
                

Types of Inheritance: 5 types

1. single
2. multiple
3. multilevel
4. hierarchical
5. hybrid

            
                